text.section:
A carrier that offers coverage to a small employer shall:
offer coverage to all of its eligible employees and all of their eligible dependents;
at the election of the small employer, offer coverage to all of its part-time employees who have a normal workweek of at least 17 1/2 but less than 30 hours per week and have been continuously employed for at least 4 consecutive months;
at the election of the small employer, offer coverage to all of its employees who are covered under another public or private plan of health insurance or another health benefit arrangement; and
establish an annual open enrollment period for self-employed individuals for at least 30 consecutive days in each 12-month period.
